des:
If you have any problem when you use this skill, you can contact us with email : support@brilliantsmart.com.au

You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light. 
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust you home light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show. 
After connecting Alexa to your Brilliant Smart products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "brilliant smart" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register one Brilliant Smart account in our "brilliant smart" app;
(3). You need to have some brilliant smart devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our "brilliant smart" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "Brilliant Smart" skill;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android, ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "Brilliant Smart" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "Brilliant Smart", and you'll be navigated to login page;
(9). Input your Brilliant Smart account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, discover new devices.”
“Alexa, turn on the bedroom light.”
“Alexa, turn off the bedroom light.”
“Alexa, set the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa, brighten the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa, dim the bedroom light to 50%.”
"Alexa, set bedroom light to green."
"Alexa, set bedroom light to cool white."

Currently this skill supports products:
smart bulb,
smart socket, 
smart heater....
